<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-22T21:04:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-22T21:04:00-05:00" n="724" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11650.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-22T19:00:00-07:04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Carranza has privately besought me, as an official who enjoys the
                            respect of the Mexican people and especially those of this party, to
                            approach our President with an earnest plea that some means be found to
                            avoid armed conflict with Mexico while giving due consideration to the
                            sensibilities of the Mexican people.</p>
                        <p>They inform me privately that the military leaders to a man united in
                            forcing Carranza to take the stand outlined in his note today relative
                            to the Tampico incident.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>